        <bioghist id="ref4">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Sybil Bailey Stockdale (1924-2015) was the wife of Vice Admiral James Bond Stockdale, United States Navy, and Prisoner of war in North Vietnam, 1965-1973. Stockdale was the National coordinator of the National League of Families of American Prisoners in Southeast Asia, and cowrote the memoir 
                <emph render="italic">In Love and War: the Story of a Family's Ordeal and Sacrifice During the Vietnam War</emph> with her husband. James and Sybil both graduated with graduate degrees from Stanford University.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref2">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The bulk of the collection contains correspondence between Sybil and James Stockdale from the begining of James' capture in Vietnam in 1965, till his release in 1973. The chronological file series maintains the original order of the creator; diaries, correspondence, notes, press releases, clippings, photographs, and phonotapes.</p>
            <p>For itemized records within each year see the attached .pdf, or the "Inventory of documents: Sybil Stockdale Archives," located in box 2. Photographs have been removed and separated to box 13, in chronological order from where they appeared in the chronological file series.</p>
        </scopecontent>
